overview: The cart comes way before the horse in the reality series "Married at First Sight." Based on a hit Danish format, "Married..." features people who agree to participate in an extreme experiment: Each covenants legal marriage with a complete stranger. Specialists -- including a spiritualist, a relationship coach and a sociologist -- use scientific matchmaking methods to determine each couple, who will not have met or had contact with each other until the wedding day. The series then documents the relationships, including honeymoons and other relatable events of married life. After several weeks, each couple must decide whether to remain together or go their individual ways.

episodes.overview: The cart comes way before the horse in the reality series "Married at First Sight." Based on a hit Danish format, "Married..." features six people who agree to participate in an extreme experiment: Each covenants legal marriage with a complete stranger. Four specialists -- a sexologist, a spiritualist, a psychologist and a sociologist -- use scientific matchmaking methods to determine each couple, who will not have met or had contact with each other until the wedding day. The series then documents the relationships, including honeymoons and other relatable events of married life. After several weeks, each pair must decide whether to remain together or go their individual ways.

episodes.name: Finale Reunion
episodes.overview: Past couples from the series discuss their thoughts about the current couples and whats happening in the episode where two months after decision day, the eight singles who got Married at First Sight reunite to talk about life away from the cameras and experts, and to answer the burning question everyone is dying to knoware they still married?

episodes.name: First Comes Marriage, Then Comes Love
episodes.overview: Five couples have only two weeks to plan their weddings, celebrate their final days of being single, and reveal to their family and friends that they are getting married to a stranger.

episodes.name: Here Comes the Stranger
episodes.overview: Five couples get ready to walk down the aisle; while the first three couples celebrate their marriages with the help of family and friends, two couples still remain to take the giant leap of faith.

episodes.name: I Married a Stranger
episodes.overview: All five couples dance the night away at their wedding receptions, before spending their first night together as husband and wife.

episodes.name: One Night Spouse
episodes.overview: All five couples have been Married at First Sight, and as the receptions come to a close, its time for them to spend their first night alone together as husband and wife. Then, after waking up next to someone they met less than 24 hours ago, each spouse will meet individually with their new stranger in-laws, before being whisked away on their honeymoon in Panama!

episodes.name: Trouble in Paradise
episodes.overview: Some of the newlyweds live out their fairy-tale love story on the tropical beaches of Panama, while other couples get off to a rocky start; tensions rise as three couples struggle to find common ground with their stranger spouses.

episodes.name: In Seasickness and in Health
episodes.overview: Four pairs of newlyweds make the most of their honeymoon with a romantic catamaran trip, while one couple remains on shore to heal their fractured marriage. But despite sunny skies, there are rough seas ahead for two pairs of stranger spouses.

episodes.name: New Wife, New Life
episodes.overview: With the thrill of the honeymoon over, five pairs of newlyweds return to Washington, D.C., to begin living together; the pressure of moving in proves to be too much for two couples, while others enjoy discovering new surprises about their new spouse.

episodes.name: Home Is Where Your Spouse Is
episodes.overview: Four pairs of newlyweds settle into married life in their new homes, while one pair struggles to find its footing; some friends are thrilled to hear how well married life is going, while others refuse to keep quiet about their concerns.

episodes.name: The "L Word"
episodes.overview: After marrying a stranger, five couples grow toward love with their stranger spouse by planning romantic surprises. But for one couple, an unexpected surprise might be the final straw for their marriage.

episodes.name: I Want You to Want Me
episodes.overview: As five pairs of newlyweds adjust to married life in their own ways, the group attends a cooking class together; while passion heats up between some couples, one couple completely melts down.

episodes.name: Anniversaries and Secrets
episodes.overview: As five couples celebrate their one-month wedding anniversaries, they've reached the crucial halfway point of the experiment. And while some couples walk hand-in-hand toward a future together, others worry that this first milestone may be the only anniversary they ever celebrate.

episodes.name: Move In or Move On
episodes.overview: All five couples sit down to take a hard look at their marriages and decide what it will take for them to stay committed until decision day; some couples cant wait to recommit, but for others the deal breakers may prove too much to handle.

episodes.name: Secrets and Lies
episodes.overview: The five married couples must embrace vulnerability, revisit their past, and expose their deepest truths; some discover new sparks, while others find themselves ready to walk away completely.

episodes.name: Fight or Flight'
episodes.overview: After one couple reaches the end of the road in their marriage, the remaining four couples go on a retreat where close quarters force them to confront their issues; tempers flare as the clock winds down to Decision Day.

episodes.name: Forever or Never
episodes.overview: As the eight-week experiment draws to a close and Decision Day looms, the four remaining couples have just a few days left to do some final soul-searching, consult with friends and family, and decide if they want to stay married or get a divorce.

episodes.name: Until Decision Day Do We Part
episodes.overview: The eight-week experiment comes to an end, as the five couples sit down with the experts to decide whether to stay married or get a divorce; some couples have their eyes on the future, while other couples are determined to get answers about the past.

episodes.name: SEASON 10 REUNION
episodes.overview: Five months after decision day, the five Washington, D.C., couples who got married at first sight reunite to look back on the good times and the hard times, discuss the ups and downs of their marriage, and reveal if they are still married.

episodes.name: Where Are They Now Special
episodes.overview: Where Are They Now Special

episodes.name: The Story Begins
episodes.overview: Nerves are high as our ten singles prepare to marry a complete stranger; one groom's motives are put to the test when the bachelor party takes a wild turn.

episodes.name: I've Never Met My Fiance
episodes.overview: Excitement is in the air and emotions run high as the wedding day begins for eight hopeful singles.

episodes.name: It's Not The First Time
episodes.overview: For the first time in Married at First Sight history, one couple already knows each other.

episodes.name: What Happened Last Night?
episodes.overview: Now that all five couples have been "Married at First Sight," it's time for them to spend their first night together as husband and wife.

episodes.name: The Honeymoon Begins
episodes.overview: The couples wake up in paradise and start to learn about the person they just married.

episodes.name: I See Red Flags
episodes.overview: As the couples enjoy the last few days of their action-packed honeymoon in Mexico, they discover more similarities and differences that will affect their marriages.

episodes.name: The Honeymoon is Over
episodes.overview: Five couples who were married at first sight return from their honeymoon and move into their new homes together, but it doesn't take long for reality to set in.

episodes.name: You Can Get Out of This!
episodes.overview: Heading into their second week of marriage, five couples adjust to daily life together while also seeking the advice of friends and family they haven't seen since marrying their stranger spouses.

episodes.name: Opening Up Is Hard To Do
episodes.overview: The couples settle into married life and begin to explore what growing in love means; some spouses declare love, while other spouses make comments that could ruin everything.

episodes.name: Dealbreakers
episodes.overview: Tensions rise when one of the participants confides in someone outside of their marriage

episodes.name: Let's Talk About Sex, Baby
episodes.overview: As our five couples find ways to grow more intimate, some of them spice up their physical relationships while others struggle to find answers to difficult questions. And one spouse shares a deal breaker that puts their marriage in jeopardy.

episodes.name: One Month Down and a Quarantine to Go
episodes.overview: The couples celebrate their one-month anniversaries in the midst of financial and intimacy challenges,

episodes.name: Home Alone
episodes.overview: For the first time in the shows history, production shuts down as the Louisiana stay-at-home order is put into place; after six weeks of the being on lockdown together, some couples move closer to love while others hit a breaking point.

episodes.name: Stranger Spouse
episodes.overview: The stay at home orders have been lifted and the couples venture out for a much-needed getaway in the country. While some renew their bonds, others begin to question if they'll want to stay married on Decision Day.

episodes.name: Pack Your Bags
episodes.overview: As Decision Day quickly approaches, our couples meet with trusted friends and family to discuss concerns about their spouses. Meanwhile, new problems arise for some, as they spend what could be their last night together as husband and wife.

episodes.name: We Need to Get a Divorce
episodes.overview: After an unprecedented four months together, enduring a pandemic and other world events, our stranger spouses have finally reached Decision Day. The couples will decide, once and for all, whether they want to stay married or get a divorce.

episodes.name: Countdown to Meltdown
episodes.overview: Ten singles get ready for the day they'll meet their mystery spouses at the altar; one bride falls apart when a gift from her husband takes her by surprise.

episodes.name: Hello, Stranger
episodes.overview: For one picky groom, his bride is not what he expected.

episodes.name: Nice to Marry You
episodes.overview: The two final weddings conclude, and all five couples meet the new families they've just married into. While some pairs feel destined for success, awkwardness abounds for others--especially when one groom has a shocking reaction to his new bride.

episodes.name: Romance or Regret
episodes.overview: Before heading on their honeymoons, the newly married couples have to meet their in-laws.

episodes.name: Last Night Was Magic
episodes.overview: On their Las Vegas honeymoon, four pairs of newlyweds learn more about their spouses; one couple deals with a secret that threatens to destroy the marriage.

episodes.name: Defending Your Wife
episodes.overview: The Vegas honeymoon continues for four newly married couples; couple number five deals with an unexpected shock, which leads to a major blowup.

episodes.name: How Do You Know If You're in Love?
episodes.overview: The newly married couples return from their honeymoon and move into their new homes together; the couples are questioned by Pastor Cal.

episodes.name: Face to Face
episodes.overview: The newlyweds meet with their friends and families for the first time since the weddings; one bride comes face to face with a stranger who will change her life.

episodes.name: Three Little Words
episodes.overview:
The couples, who married as strangers just two and a half weeks ago, explore the potential to fall in love in the real world. And while some couples are inching closer and closer toward the "L" word,

others find themselves barely past the starting line.

episodes.name: Third Week's a Charm
episodes.overview: Three weeks after being married at first sight, some couples struggle to start over while others face challenges that seem insurmountable. Luckily, Dr. Viviana is in town to offer help and hope.

episodes.name: The Monthiversary
episodes.overview: Approaching the first milestone, the couples are reminded of the commitment they made to a complete stranger one month ago. While some celebrate this achievement, others question their future with their spouses.

episodes.name: Must Love Dogs
episodes.overview: All five husbands have become dog dads since marrying their stranger spouses. Some take on the responsibility with love and excitement, but for others, it causes a severe emotional backlash.

episodes.name: Unanswered Questions
episodes.overview: With Decision Day less than three weeks away, the couples meet individually with Dr. Pepper and Pastor Cal to probe the serious questions they still have about their marriage.

episodes.name: I Expected a Little Better
episodes.overview: With only two weeks left until Decision Day, the four couples revisit their pasts with the hopes of solidifying their marriages for the future.

episodes.name: Retreat Ready
episodes.overview: With only nine days left to Decision Day, the couples travel to Hilton Head, S.C., for a break from their normal married lives, an adventure that could bring them closer together or expose the cracks in their foundations.

episodes.name: Speak Now or Forever Hold Your Peace
episodes.overview: With the gravity of Decision Day looming, each husband and wife engages in important conversations with their loved ones.

episodes.name: Real Life Starts Now
episodes.overview: The journey for five couples who were married at first sight comes to a shocking and dramatic conclusion.

episodes.name: Reunion, Part 2
episodes.overview: The Atlanta reunion continues as Chris' fight with Pastor Dwight concludes, Haley and Jacob awkwardly reflect on their marriage and the Experts weigh in on their matches.

episodes.name: Where Are They Now?
episodes.overview: Four months after decision day, the couples from Atlanta are back as both the newlyweds and the newly single give updates on how their lives have changed since the cameras went away.

episodes.name: Hall of Fame
episodes.overview: Hall of Fame: Jamie Otis shares some of his favorite moments of the show in celebration of 12 seasons and takes nominations for that Married at First Sight Hall of Fame, including categories such as Favorite Fairytale and Least Likely to Succeed.

episodes.name: Lone Stars No More

episodes.name: Houston, We Have A Marriage
episodes.overview: Wedding day continues as four more couples prepare to walk down the aisle to marry a complete stranger; nerves set in as the clock counts down, and one bride's finicky ways could set her up for failure.

episodes.name: Their First Rodeo
episodes.overview: After the final two couples get married, the brides and grooms enjoy their first dinners, first dances, and first introductions to family; and when they head to bed together for the very first time, sparks fly for some, while others put up barriers.

episodes.name: One Day Down, A Lifetime to Go
episodes.overview: For the first time, the five couples are waking up married to a stranger; before they can leave on their honeymoon, each spouse will have brunch with their new in-laws.

episodes.name: The Keys to My Heart
episodes.overview: Five pairs of newly-wed strangers are whisked away to the Florida Keys and begin the journey of learning who they've just married; while one groom learns that his bride is very hard to please, another couple's honeymoon is over before it even begins.

episodes.name: Out of the Comfort Zone and Into the Sea
episodes.overview: The honeymoon continues in the Florida Keys for just four of our couples. Despite trying exciting new activities and taking stabs at romance, some start to learn that their differences are greater than they imagined.

episodes.name: Home, Not Alone
episodes.overview: The couples return to Houston to live together for the first time as husband and wife, but settling into day-to-day life is a rough transition for anyone. Now our stranger spouses are challenged with the struggles of everyday life and the decision to fight for their marriages--or flee from them.

episodes.name: Family & Friends & Feelings, Oh My!
episodes.overview: As the newly-married couples dive into domestic life and welcome friends to housewarming parties, one husband sees red flags, while another wonders if he was ready for marriage at all.

episodes.name: Could This Be Love?
episodes.overview: One of the couples considers saying they love each other as the other four pairs attempt to find the spark between them.

episodes.name: Locked Out
episodes.overview: Dr. Viviana gives our five couples some sexy assignments to help build trust and intimacy; while some couples enjoy the added spice, others feel distance from their partner.

episodes.name: Caution: Feelings Approaching
episodes.overview: Having reached their one month milestone, love is growing for some, but one husband is fed up with his wife's lies; an unforeseen death alters the course of another couple's journey.

episodes.name: Is There Someone Else?
episodes.overview: As the couples settle into everyday life, some look forward to their future together, while others begin to question everything; when one bride calls for an expert intervention, things get intense quickly.

episodes.name: Tears, Jeers, and 25 Cent Martinis
episodes.overview: With decision day looming, the spouses meet with the experts to discuss unanswered questions about their marriages.

episodes.name: Country Chaos
episodes.overview: With only two weeks until Decision Day, the couples travel to a ranch in the country for a break from their everyday lives.

episodes.name: Memory Lane & a Dirty Little Secret
episodes.overview: With less than two weeks until Decision Day, the spouses revisit their pasts in order to discover more about one another; when a secret is revealed within one couple, it threatens to break their marriage and future.

episodes.name: Reunion Pt. 1
episodes.overview: The Houston cast reunites with host Kevin Frazier to discuss their eventful season and what has happened since Decision Day.

episodes.name: The Weddings are Coming! The Weddings Are Coming!
episodes.overview: Ten newly-engaged Bostonians have only two weeks until they meet their stranger spouses at the altar; one groom's antics at the bachelor party leaves raises questions on his willingness to settle down, and one bride finds her wedding overwhelming.

episodes.name: Nice Day for a Wicked Wedding
episodes.overview: One couple ties the knot, but four other sets of strangers prepare for the biggest day of their lives; stress builds and reality sets in, leaving one bride unsure of her decision, while an independent groom hopes that married life will suit him.

episodes.name: Bliss, Brunches and Brawls... Oh My!
episodes.overview: The four remaining singles become legally bound in marriage, and receptions kick into high gear as the couples get to know their spouses' family and friends.

episodes.name: It's Not a Shore Thing
episodes.overview: Five couples wake up in Puerto Rico to start learning more about the strangers they just married.

episodes.name: Dark Side of the Honeymoon
episodes.overview: The Puerto Rico honeymoon continues in as five couples try to enjoy the sun, sand, and their still-unfamiliar spouses; trouble brews in paradise as some newlyweds struggle to forge a connection before their return to Boston.

episodes.name: This Is My Decision Day
episodes.overview: Four and a half couples move in with their new spouses as Pastor Cal guides them into the next chapter of marriage.

episodes.name: Striking a Balance
episodes.overview: The lives of our couples merge even more as they invite friends and family to housewarming parties. Later, a surprising rift is caused by boiling noodles, and a trip to a bowling alley ends up in the gutter.

episodes.name: Is Love on the Table?
episodes.overview: Still new to their marriages to strangers, the spouses explore deeper feelings; as they dig into each other's past loves, some couples seize the opportunity to get closer, while others teeter on the edge of heartbreak.

episodes.name: Mighty Mighty Boston Bonds
episodes.overview: The stakes go up for the Boston newlyweds as they seek to strengthen their bonds of trust and intimacy; the couples consult an expert, ask tough questions, and try to improve their emotional and physical closeness.

episodes.name: Worst. Dinner Party. Ever!
episodes.overview: The couples celebrate their one-month anniversaries with gifts, boat rides, and getting back to nature; things seem to be moving in the right direction for everyone, until a scandalous discovery comes up at a group dinner.

episodes.name: Settling In, or Just Settling?
episodes.overview: Activities like driving lessons and cooking meals take centre stage as the couples settle into domestic life; the realities of unemployment, budgets and even the simple division of chores create issues that begin to drive a wedge between the pairs.

episodes.name: Popping the Questions
episodes.overview: Dr. Pepper and Pastor Cal meet individually with the spouses to uncover questions that may still be lingering in their marriages; the answers aren't always what the couples hope to hear; one person's meeting with an expert sparks fireworks.

episodes.name: It's Just a Blip
episodes.overview: With just two weeks left until Decision Day, the four couples head to Vermont for a last romantic getaway; despite sound baths, adventure parks, and fun with alpacas, not everything is fun and games, especially when one person ends up in urgent care

episodes.name: Are You in, or Are you out?
So Ready in SoCal
episodes.overview: The ten brave San Diego residents have only two weeks to prepare before they meet their spouses at the altar; for one, a family member's disapproval could create an irreparable rift; on the big day, an emotionally-guarded bride becomes a puddle of tears.

episodes.name: Whole Wife for a Whole Life?
episodes.overview: With one wedding down and four to go, the soon-to-be spouses anxiously prepare to say "I do" to a stranger; however, when one groom gets terrible news, a wedding has to be postponed for the first time in "Married at First Sight" history.

episodes.name: Ain't No Wedding Like a West Coast Wedding
episodes.overview: While one pair of strangers faces an uncertain future, four other couples celebrate their weddings under the San Diego sun. Cakes are cut, garters are tossed, and the question of wedding night sex is in the air.

episodes.name: Sand, Sun, and Spouses
episodes.overview: Four newlywed couples, who have never met each other before, spend their first night together, sharing stories, secrets, and a bed. In the morning, each is bombarded with personal questions from their spouse's friends and family. Then it's time for sun in the fun as they jet off to a honeymoon in Mexico.

episodes.name: Everything Whale Be Okay
episodes.overview: In Puerto Vallarta, the newlyweds enjoy their honeymoon of paddleboarding, horseback riding and whale watching; one husband surprises his wife with the words "I love you," but another spouse makes a much more unpleasant declaration.

episodes.name: Saved By The Mariachis!
episodes.overview: Things get hot in Mexico as the honeymoons continue for the newlyweds; one groom suddenly drops the L word; another groom can't see past the eight-week mark; another betrays his new wife's trust when he reveals her biggest secret to others.

episodes.name: Real Life Reckoning
episodes.overview: The couples move into their new apartment together; Pastor Cal visits to help; while one couple takes their relationship to the next level, another must navigate a shocking encounter between their dogs that threatens to tear their marriage apart.

episodes.name: Party Ways
episodes.overview: Five newlywed couples settle into their lives in San Diego and prep to be reunited with friends and family for the first time since their weddings; they plan their first housewarming parties together; grievances are aired and advice is shared.

episodes.name: Are You Going to Gaslight Me?
episodes.overview: As the newlywed strangers enter their third week of marriage, the topic of love is on everyone's minds; deep questions lead to unexpected revelations, and spouses have to face uncompromising attitudes and unforgiven mistakes.

episodes.name: Moody Monthiversaries
episodes.overview: As they celebrate their one-month anniversaries, the couples reflect on their progress and set their sights on the road to Decision Day; while some seek to recapture the magic they've lost, others struggle to foster trust.

episodes.name: Back to Our Future
episodes.overview: Having just passed the one month milestone in their marriages, the husbands and wives open up further to their spouses by returning to their roots and sharing more about their pasts; the couples work to build a stronger future together.

episodes.name: Baby Steps
episodes.overview: When Dr. Pia returns, trust is put to the test and intimacy soars as one couple shares a steamy getaway and another gets a special delivery; two marriages could be headed for trouble if compromises can't be reached before it's too late.

episodes.name: The Ugly Truth
episodes.overview: The couples have one final chance to speak with the experts as Decision Day draws near; Dr. Pepper, Pastor Cal and DeVon Franklin help the couples confront truths; one couple finds it difficult to continue on, while another is ready to go all in.

episodes.name: No Hug For You
episodes.overview: The wives and husbands embark on a couples retreat, where one wife is treated to her very first prom; while there's laughter, dancing, and the promise of sex for some, there are dramatic outbursts and tears for others.

episodes.name: Are You My Person?
episodes.overview: With Decision Day just over a week away, the anxiety increases for everyone; one couple finds out if absence really does make the heart grow fonder, while another struggles with a difficult goodbye.

episodes.name: This Isn't Best Friends at First Sight
episodes.overview: The clock nearly runs out, and the couples have only a few days until Decision Day; the last chance arrives to answer any remaining questions, and it ruins the final night for one couple and challenges others.

episodes.name: This Was Supposed to be Our New Start
episodes.overview: It's time for the couples to take control of their marriages and their futures as they make the decision to stay married or get a divorce. But as they prepare to move forward from the experiment, a shocking realization leads one couple to reverse their decision.

episodes.name: San Diego Reunion, Part 1
episodes.overview: Emotions run deep as the San Diego couples reunite to reveal stunning secrets from their season and surprising updates on their current relationships. As they relive their most romantic, hilarious and dramatic moments, two cast members come to a tense showdown over shocking allegations.

episodes.name: San Diego Reunion, Part 2
episodes.overview: The San Diego cast struggles to deal with the aftermath of a heated confrontation. Issues from the past continue to put pressure on their relationships as they move forward. The MAFS experts intervene with some blunt words of wisdom to help with wounds that have still not healed.

episodes.name: Where Are They Now: San Diego
episodes.overview: Five months after Decision Day, the San Diego couples navigate their new reality as they move forward with their relationships and lives. While one couple is on the verge of separation, another struggles to see eye to eye as they contemplate a major decision. After an explosive reunion, tensions are still high among the group as they all reunite one last time to say goodbye to one of their own.

episodes.name: Marry Me in Tennessee
episodes.overview: In Nashville, Tenn., 10 singles have just found out that they'll be marrying a complete stranger in two short weeks; at the bachelorette party, one bride-to-be raises her eyebrows when she gets flirty with a stripper; a groom's emotions take over.

episodes.name: Runaway Groom?
episodes.overview: It's wedding day; five Nashville, Tenn., couples anxiously prepare to marry a complete stranger; starting with the I do's and awkward kisses, the stranger spouses begin their eight-week marital journey.

episodes.name: Music City Matrimony
episodes.overview: The final two couples tie the knot in Nashville, Tenn.; the 10 newlyweds share their first dinner and dance; one bride refuses to share a first kiss; everyone is wondering what is going to happen in the honeymoon suite.

episodes.name: Honeymoon Hiccups
episodes.overview: Five newlywed pairs of strangers share a bed for the first time on their wedding night; they are dropped into the lion's den for a round of personal questions and concerns from their brand-new spouse's family and friends.

episodes.name: It's All About the Journey
episodes.overview: Five pairs of newlyweds strangers honeymoon in Jamaica; some spouses see red flags when they learn that their partners are not very adventurous; one couple inches closer to saying, "I love you"; a revelation leaves one bride questioning her husband.

episodes.name: You Dropped a Bomb on Me
episodes.overview: One wife wants to pick up the pace; her husband hides his reason for wanting to slow things down; some wives start to question their husbands' sense of humour; a comment from one husband threatens to ruin his marriage before the honeymoon is over.

episodes.name: Jamaican Me Crazy
episodes.overview: The five couples share final moments together in paradise; one couple fights their way back to common ground; a heart-to-heart does more harm than good; the couples travel back to Nashville, Tenn., where the shared spaces will deepen some bonds.

episodes.name: Poised for Battle
episodes.overview: Visits to their spouse's homes reveal surprises for the couple; two couples experience cold feet about moving in as another marriage heats up; Pastor Cal pays a visit to ask some tough questions.

episodes.name: Party-ing Ways
episodes.overview: The Nashville newlyweds plan housewarming parties, but the guest list sparks controversy for one couple, and steak isn't the only thing getting grilled; one couple reveals they've crossed the threshold into sex, and another reconsiders their divorce.

episodes.name: Love Is Up in the Air
episodes.overview: Some spouses confront deep questions and look inward, while other couples try to build love through shared adventures; after all the sailing, spa nights and heart-to-hearts, not all the couples are seeing eye to eye.

episodes.name: Moonshine and Monthiversaries
episodes.overview: The newlywed strangers celebrate their one-month anniversaries, with some taking to the skies, others to the water and one couple smashing stuff up; after uncomfortable questions at a dinner, one couple questions whether they're on the same page.

episodes.name: Getting to the Crust
episodes.overview: Fear gets the better of one bride as she worries that her happy marriage will crumble; another wife clams up when her husband finally begins to share; a sensual body painting session turns one wife's body into a masterpiece.

episodes.name: I'm Not Acting Crazy With You Tonight
episodes.overview: The couples go back to their roots and share the memories that made them who they are; while some couples get into the tough and sad moments of their past, others struggle to open up; one wife's outrageous demand has her husband second guessing

episodes.name: The Rope, the Feather and the Bidet
episodes.overview: With two weeks left until Decision Day, the couples face tests as Dr. Pia returns to help with their intimacy and sex lives; while one couple almost reaches a breaking point, another finds hope in a steamy exercise.

episodes.name: Whiskey a No-No
episodes.overview: With less than two weeks left until Decision Day, flowing whiskey at a couples' get-together leads to shocking confessions, and a husband's dancing "misstep" leaves one already unsteady marriage teetering on the edge.

episodes.name: Un-BEAR-able Truth
episodes.overview: The couples head to a breathtaking mountain getaway for a dual birthday bash, bear sightings, and crowning the first-ever "Married at First Sight" king.

episodes.name: Gatlinburg Getaway
episodes.overview: The newlyweds continue their couples retreat in the Great Smoky Mountains; bonding through adventurous activities like pole climbing and log rolling, the couples work to strengthen their connection and settle any unresolved issues.

episodes.name: What's Our Safe Word?
episodes.overview: Things heat up--on the pole and in the bedroom--for a couple that was still hoping for a spark to ignite; others meet with friends and family for insights into whether their marriages can last.

episodes.name: Sliding Toward Decision Day
episodes.overview: With Decision Day around the corner, one husband's lingering doubts leave his wife wondering if he will ever be satisfied; meanwhile, a group of flirtatious singles gives the wives a glimpse at what life after Decision Day could look like.

episodes.name: Our Last Rodeo
episodes.overview: After eight weeks of being married to a stranger, the time has finally come for the couples to decide if they want to stay married or get a divorce; when unsaid things are finally said, it forces partners to reconsider their decisions.

episodes.name: The Final Decision
episodes.overview: With the final couple's decision being made, the newly married and newly divorced begin anew. But some decisions don't sit well, and tensions begin to boil for one couple. Meanwhile, another couple legally binds themselves together even more tightly.

episodes.name: First Dates and Swapping Mates
episodes.overview: With Decision Day behind them, our ten individuals embark on their lives post-experimenteither as happily married, or back in the dating pool once again. A first date with a mystery man leaves one former wife with a renewed hope for love, while another first date ends with a former husband seeing red. And the chemistry is hot when two former spouses steam things up making lattes.

episodes.name: Last Call for Music City
episodes.overview: In the season finale, our Nashville couples continue to navigate life after Decision Day. While one couple remains married, four others face the harsh reality of divorce and finding love again in Music City. From a tail-wagging soiree, to hurling hatchets, the individuals prepare to bid farewell to the cameras. But will an unexpected hookup send shockwaves through the group?

episodes.name: Cast Tell All
episodes.overview: An outspoken, emotional and confrontational group of former cast members reveal shocking secrets and surprising insights as they share the inside scoop on the Married At First Sight experience. They spill the tea on what really happened behind the scenes during the series' most unforgettable moments and give updates on all the gossip about their fellow cast members. Two former cast mates face off over their complicated relationship.

episodes.name: Season 16 Reunion Part 1
episodes.overview: The entire Nashville cast returns to discuss the most controversial moments from their season and reveal shocking updates on their lives and relationships. Emotions are at an all-time high as unsettled issues cause tension amongst the group and one couple questions if they made the right choice on Decision Day.

episodes.name: Season 16 Reunion Part 2
episodes.overview: More secrets are revealed and evolving relationships are put to the test as the Nashville cast continues to reflect on their unforgettable season. As one couple struggles to overcome the mistakes of their past, another looks forward to the potential of a new future together. Tough questions from the MAFS experts cause tearful regret.

16.name: Nashville
16.overview: It's Nashville Nuptials! Married at First Sight heads to Nashville, Tenn., for its sixteenth season where 10 singles will undergo their journey to meet the potential loves of their lives during this 23-episode season.

episodes.name: Mile High Matrimony
episodes.overview: In Denver, 10 singles take the plunge to marry strangers, sight unseen in two weeks; among them, an inexperienced bride questions her decision, while a groom's girthy secret shocks everyone; the countdown to the weddings is on.

episodes.name: Rocky Mountain Romance
episodes.overview: With one pair having already exchanged their vows in Denver, the other eight singles make the final preparations for their own mile high matrimonies, but on wedding day, their anxieties reach a pinnacle.

episodes.name: Hard Launch
episodes.overview: With only one couple left to meet their new spouse at the altar, these former singles jump into marriage headfirst; these newlyweds try to learn as much about each other as possible before spending their first night together as husband and wife.

episodes.name: Goodbye Single Life, Hello Marriage
episodes.overview: The couples return to their honeymoon suites; a miscommunication leaves one bride feeling insecure; a frustrated bride confronts her husband who is left with more questions than answers; a shocking revelation blindsides the couples.

episodes.name: Take Me Down to Paradise City
episodes.overview: The newlywed couples head to Cancun, Mexico, to start their honeymoon; sandy beaches and the clear ocean water help set the tone as they try to grow their connection to last a lifetime; one couple must overcome a roadblock.

episodes.name: Cancun Can't Touch This
episodes.overview: As the couples enjoy their honeymoon in Cancun, Mexico, one couple grapples with their cultural differences and the impact they have on their marriage; one wife doesn't know why she and her husband aren't keeping pace with the other couples.

episodes.name: A Honeymoon Rockier Than the Mountains
episodes.overview: A husband shuts down when his wife asks a question that's too personal; wife gets judged for asking the wrong question; one husband has to deal with a medical emergency; one couple has a mountain to get over.

episodes.name: Divorce, Prayers and Spider Scares
episodes.overview: Back in Denver after their honeymoon, the couples explore each other's homes; the couples grapple with ending their journey as newlyweds when they're faced with the tough decision of hitting the reset button or seeking a divorce.

episodes.name: Wigging Out
episodes.overview: As the newlyweds are only just beginning to navigate the challenges of living with a stranger spouse, they host their first housewarming party together; but not all is fun and games as tensions flare and quickly devolve into a shouting match.

episodes.name: Breaking Up the Party
episodes.overview: The couple's meet up for a potluck dinner, but the fun is quickly dampened by some explosive news; Dr. Pia visits the couples just in the nick of time as new challenges present themselves.

episodes.name: Taking It Day by Day
episodes.overview: The spouses spend their one-month anniversaries ice skating, skiing and exploring the mountains on horseback, but not everyone is in the mood to celebrate; a husband's text message leaves his wife in tears.

episodes.name: Something's Fishy
episodes.overview: With Decision Day less than four weeks away, the couples work to navigate the uncharted waters of their new lives together. And while some are left broken hearted, a new journey, and a second chance at love, are beginning for another.

episodes.name: Exploring Intimacy at an Altitude
episodes.overview: The couples get creative in an attempt to deepen their connections, but when one wife speaks her truth, her husband is left blindsided; the countdown to "I do" begins for the last pair as the groom wonders if the second time will be the charm.

episodes.name: New Groom, Who Dis?
episodes.overview: After getting jilted at the altar the first time, one groom gets an historic second chance to be married at first sight, but his bride might refuse to marry him; the drama between the other couples could ruin what might have been a happy day.

episodes.name: Honeyspoonin'
episodes.overview: With one honeymoon in full effect, the other couples face intense issues of honesty and trust; with decision day on the horizon, the couples look to the experts for guidance in their decision of whether they should stay married or get a divorce.

episodes.name: Rocky Retreat
episodes.overview: The final honeymoon is over, and the newlyweds return to Denver to face a mountain of new challenges. Outside the city, the others gather for a relaxing retreat, and while some have high hopes of deepening their bond, others are on an outright collision course.

episodes.name: Crash and Bond
episodes.overview: The couple's retreat is rocked by a life-threatening injury, which leads to new perspectives; with Decision Day around the corner, the couples work to strengthen their bonds before having to make one of the most important decisions of their lives.

episodes.name: In Sickness & Suspicion
episodes.overview: With decision day approaching fast, some couples begin to see things in a different light; the newlyweds gain new insight when they gather their friends for a housewarming party; a familiar face returns with a surprising revelation.

episodes.name: Sex, Lies & Questionable Behavior
episodes.overview: With decision day less than a week away for most of our couples, the husbands and wives make one last effort to decide if they want to spend the rest of their lives with their spouse.

episodes.name: Decision Day Round One
episodes.overview: The day has finally come for most of our couples as the fate of their futures rests on their answers for Decision Day. With the weight of such a heavy decision on their shoulders, some look to find peace within their relationship, while others look to find a way forward and stay married. But the boiling tension threatens all couples as the pressure of the day leads to unescapable confrontations and irreversible damage.

episodes.name: Climbing Down From Decision Day
episodes.overview: The shocking aftermath of Decision Day leads to some second guessing and self-reflecting for most of our couples. Meanwhile our couple on their own journey celebrates their one-month anniversary, but when they start sharing their thoughts for the future, doubts start creeping in.

episodes.name: Doubts, Dilemmas and Drag!
episodes.overview: Post-Decision Day complexities persist as our couples navigate life changes with fitness pursuits, exploring the art of metal forging and even enjoying a dazzling drag show. Meanwhile, the last couple approaching their Decision Day grapples with doubts and uncertainties about their future. With less than a week remaining before their pivotal decision, the question looms: will they choose to stay married or get a divorce?

episodes.name: Second Time's the Charm?
episodes.overview: Most of our couples continue to navigate life after Decision Day; and as they build a path forward, they face one more decision, to either build a new life with their exes, or without them. And on our final Decision Day, will the foundation theyve built allow their marriage to soar, or will the weight of uncertainty bring it all crashing down?

episodes.name: Denver Reunion, Part 1
episodes.overview: Tensions are high as the entire Denver cast returns to revisit the most shocking moments from their season and reveal why their relationships have become so contentious. Accusations of deception, manipulation and cheating create even more animosity with the group as they struggle to sort out their differences.

episodes.name: Denver Reunion, Part 2
episodes.overview: The Denver cast returns for part two of the season 17 reunions and the emotions are at an all-time high; the cast challenges one another on their truths and when a shocking new secret is exposed, there are tears, animosity and bonds broken forever.

17.name: Denver
17.overview: In Denver, 10 singles take the plunge to marry strangers, sight unseen in two weeks.

episodes.name: Chicago Hopefuls
episodes.overview: In Chicago Illinois, ten singles make the riskiest decision they have ever made; to marry a complete and total stranger. Pre wedding jitters present themselves in different ways. From spilling too much tea to bawling their eyes out, one thing is clear; the risk is worth the reward of everlasting love. But for one nervous bride, the jitters may be too much to bear.

episodes.name: Windy City Weddings
episodes.overview: The wedding day continues in the Windy City where 8 more singles prepare to meet their spouses at the altar. As the pressure mounts and the moment of truth approaches, hopes and wishes are pondered as one bride puts her full trust in the Universe, and one groom holds a secret that could doom his marriage.

episodes.name: Did Ya'll Meet My Husband?
episodes.overview: The final couple finally meet at the altar and then it's time for the wedding receptions to begin! And while some couples are immediately drawn to each other, one bride is quickly overwhelmed, while one groom reveals a secret about his past that could derail his marriage on the first day.

episodes.name: Wedding Bliss or a Miss
episodes.overview: In the morning after the weddings, a myriad of concerns arise amidst the joy of newlywed life, including financial worries, age gaps, and the revelation of a spouse still living at home. During family brunches, unease deepens with a father's request for STI testing and another spouse's pursuit of perfection. But despite doubts about attraction and some hesitations, the journey begins as our couples embark on their honeymoons.

episodes.name: A Beach of a Honeymoon
episodes.overview: Our ten newlyweds enjoy their honeymoon in the beautiful Mexican Riviera, and begin to explore all aspects of the strangers they just married. As most couples bond over deep conversations and fun activities in paradise, one couple fights to find a connection. Could their marriage be over before they return to Chicago?

episodes.name: Never Forget About Karla
episodes.overview: As their honeymoon comes to an end, four of the couples look to build on their blossoming marriages while one couple looks to try and put the pieces back together again. Then, back in Chicago, real life hits hard as they settle into their new lives as husband and wife.
